<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583150>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 4. Underwater photographs of nuptial males and females of Enneapterygius phoenicosoma n. sp. A, nuptial male, off Nobeoka, Miyazaki Prefecture, east coast of Kyushu, Japan, 0–2m depth, 5 August 2007 (photo by K. Ota); B, nuptial male, off east coast of Izu Peninsula, Japan, 6–10 m depth (photo by S. Yamamoto); C, nuptial male, off Kii Peninsula, Japan, 11–15 m depth, 12 October 2008 (photo by D. Itou); D, nuptial male and two females, off Otsuki, Kochi Prefecture, Shikoku, Japan, 5m depth, 29 October 2014 (photo by K. Matsuno). Live nuptial males have a reddish body with a black head and pectoral-fin base, a distinct white band along the posterior margin of the black area on the pectoral-fin base, and no dense black fins." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4583150/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583146>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 3. Female of Enneapterygius phoenicosoma n. sp. KAUM–I. 40970, paratype, 28.6mm SL, Ichiki-kushikino, Kagoshima, Japan. The two photographs represent the same individual." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4583146/files/figure.png" .

