<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4583142>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 2. Males of Enneapterygius phoenicosoma n. sp. from Ichiki-kushikino, Kagoshima, Japan. A, KAUM–I. 40972, paratype, 31.0mm SL; B, KAUM–I. 40973, paratype, 31.7mm SL. In each case, the preserved specimen and the underwater photograph represent the same individual. Underwater photographs taken at depths of 0.1–0.5m show the normal coloration of males, and the coloration changes to the nuptial coloration immediately after death." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4583142/files/figure.png" .
